Aspen Kartier banned from Twitch after dog abuse backlash is currently trending after a disturbing livestream clip went viral on January 29, 2026. This Aspen Kartier banned from Twitch after dog abuse backlash update details the moment viewers were left in shock when audio of repeated yelping was heard during a live broadcast.
In the viral clip, the rapper-turned-streamer is heard asking her dog how it escaped its cage before a series of thumping sounds and distressing yelps follow, leading many to believe the animal was being struck. The footage ends with Aspen carrying the dog out of the room by its scruff. Following an immediate and massive outcry from the community and animal rights advocates, Twitch has officially issued an indefinite ban on her account, which had over 70,000 followers. While Aspen has yet to release a full formal statement, the "Queen of the South" artist is facing a wave of de-platforming calls across YouTube and TikTok.

description:
India is moving closer to launching its first high-speed bullet train, and officials have now given a target date. The Union Railway Minister has said that the countryâ€™s first bullet train service is expected to begin operations on August 15, 2027, which is Indiaâ€™s Independence Day. The initial section of the project will start running before the full route is completed, so passengers can experience high-speed travel earlier.

The train will operate on the Mumbaiâ€“Ahmedabad high-speed rail corridor, a major new rail line being built between Maharashtra and Gujarat. This corridor is around 508 kilometres long, and the bullet trains on it are designed to travel at speeds of up to around 300â€“320 km/h, cutting travel time drastically compared with regular trains. The first phase may begin with a shorter segment between places like Surat and Bilimora or Vapi, with more sections opening in stages over time.

The full Mumbaiâ€“Ahmedabad route is expected to be completed by 2029, but the government is aiming to have the first operational stretch ready by mid-2027. This would mark a historic moment for Indian rail travel and introduce true high-speed services in the country for the first time.

title: The Quiet Wedding Dress That Became Iconic | Julie Andrews â€“ The Sound of Music (1965)
description:
This is one of the most understated wedding dresses in film history â€” and thatâ€™s exactly why it became unforgettable.
Worn by Julie Andrews as Maria in The Sound of Music (1965), this ivory silk shantung gown was designed by legendary costume designer Dorothy Jeakins.
With its high collar, long fitted sleeves, fabric-covered buttons, and soft A-line train, the dress reflects Mariaâ€™s journey from novitiate to bride â€” quiet, graceful, and deeply intentional.
No sparkle. No excess. Just craftsmanship, structure, and timeless elegance.
Even though the gown leans more toward 1950s bridal style than the filmâ€™s 1930s setting, it remains one of the most beloved wedding dresses in cinema history.
